# Weekly content & SEO atomic push

## Intent

One indexed asset live each week (blog post, changelog, doc page): topic chosen against keyword + ICP, draft generated with AI then human-edited, on-page SEO complete, shared on 2 channels.

## Scope

One indexed asset live each week (blog post, changelog, doc page): topic chosen against keyword + ICP, draft generated with AI then human-edited, on-page SEO complete, shared on 2 channels.

## Stages

### 1. Pick the topic

Choose against keyword + ICP, not vibes.

Tasks:
- Pull the keyword gap list
- Cross-check ICP pain themes
- Pick the single topic for this week

Outputs:
- Chosen topic
- Primary keyword
- ICP angle

Decision gate: Advance only when topic ties to a tracked keyword AND ICP pain.

### 2. Outline + draft

AI-draft the bones, you sharpen the spine.

Tasks:
- AI-generate the outline from research notes
- Draft with the AI tool
- Human-edit for voice and hard truths

Outputs:
- Outline doc
- Draft v1
- Human-edit pass

Decision gate: Advance only when human-edit pass is complete (no AI-default sentences).

### 3. On-page SEO

Cover the boring but high-leverage details.

Tasks:
- Run the on-page SEO checklist (title, meta, headings, schema)
- Add internal links to the topical cluster
- Optimise images and core web vitals

Outputs:
- On-page checklist done
- Internal link map
- Image/CWV pass

Decision gate: Advance only when checklist is 100% green.

### 4. Publish + index nudge

Get it live and indexed fast.

Tasks:
- Publish to the site
- Submit URL to search indexing tools
- Add to the sitemap and RSS

Outputs:
- Live URL
- Submission receipts
- Sitemap update

Decision gate: Advance only when URL is live AND indexed.

### 5. Distribute on 2 channels

Push out where the ICP lives.

Tasks:
- Cross-post a short version to X / IH / LinkedIn
- Drop it in the newsletter
- Reply in 2 relevant threads with the link

Outputs:
- Channel posts
- Newsletter inclusion
- Thread replies

Decision gate: Cycle closes when 2 channels have actually shipped a post.

## Common pitfalls

- Skipping the decision-gate write-up to keep moving - closes the loop with vibes, not evidence.
- Treating each stages outputs as optional - every output is a gate input for the next stage.
- Letting one bad week stretch a fixed-cadence ritual into a quarterly one.

## Quality checklist

- Every stage has at least one referenced methodology that resolves under `knowledge/`.
- Every output is a real artefact, not a feeling.
- The final decision is a written commitment, not we will see.
